"```sql\nSELECT Patient.ID, Patient.SEX, Patient.Birthday\nFROM Patient\nJOIN Laboratory ON Patient.ID = Laboratory.ID\nWHERE Laboratory.WBC <= 3.5 OR Laboratory.WBC >= 9.0\nGROUP BY Patient.SEX, Patient.ID, Patient.Birthday\nORDER BY Patient.Birthday ASC;\n```\n\nThis SQL query selects the patient ID, sex, and birthday for patients who have an abnormal white blood cell count, as defined by the evidence. It groups the results by sex and orders the patients by age in ascending order, which is achieved by ordering by the birthday in ascending order."